/-
SU(9) = A₈ is a Lie subalgebra of E₈ — closure verification
================================================================

Verifies that for every pair (i,j) of SU(9) basis elements,
the E₈ bracket [B_i, B_j] contains only SU(9) basis elements.
80 SU(9) generators inside 248 E₈ generators.

SU(9) = A₈ is a maximal subgroup of E₈, obtained by removing node 2
from the extended E₈ Dynkin diagram. The A₈ simple roots are
{α₁, α₃, α₄, α₅, α₆, α₇, α₈, -θ} where θ is the highest root.

The A₈ root system (72 roots) was computed by SageMath:
  - BFS from A₈ simple roots, collecting all E₈ roots reachable
    by adding/subtracting A₈ simple roots
  - A₈ Cartan matrix verified as tridiagonal (2,-1,-1,2) pattern

Decomposition: 248 = 80 (adjoint SU(9)) + 84 (Λ³C⁹) + 84* (Λ³C⁹*)
  - 80 generators close under bracket [verified here]
  - 84 + 84* = 168 generators form the complement

Generated by scripts/sage_su9_in_e8.py (SageMath oracle).

References:
  - Slansky, "Group theory for unified model building" Phys. Rep. 79 (1981)
  - Adams, "Lectures on Exceptional Lie Groups" (1996)
  - Wilson, "Uniqueness of an E₈ model" J. Math. Phys. 63 (2022)
  - e8_sparse_defs.lean: E₈ bracket table
  - e8_so16_subalgebra.lean: pattern source (SO(16) ⊂ E₈)
-/

import clifford.e8_sparse_defs

set_option maxHeartbeats 4000000

open E8Sparse

